parameters: \N<Resident>They've come... The Luda soldiers are really here...!?
\N<Resident>You can't go any further from here... Please turn back...

\N<Officer Luda>What do you think you're doing? Our march won't be hindered
by the likes of you, move aside at once.
\N<Resident>...I can't. The lives of my wife and children are at stake.

\N<Officer Luda>Hmph... I see, it must be Zeda's doing. It's just like him
to take wives and children hostage, and then use you all as
his shields. But unfortunately for you, that's not going to
happen.
\N<Resident>We can't just let you through easily either...!

\N<Hebeta>(They don't look like they have any combat experience at
all. Yet they stand in front of us Luda soldiers.)

\N<Hebeta>(I don't understand... He said it's for his wife... Could
this possibly be what love is...?)

\N<Resident>Please... Just go back. The ones you call Zeda promised to
release the hostages if we do this.

\N<Officer Luda>Are you fools? There's no way he would keep such a promise.
Stand aside.

\N<Resident>I can't...! Even if there's a chance he won't keep his
promise, this is the only thing we can do!

\N<Officer Luda>Don't be so mistaken. Our mission is solely to capture the
rebel Zeda, not to rescue you or your wives and children.

\N<Officer Luda>In other words... It doesn't matter what happens to you or
your families.
\N<Resident>Wha...!!??
\N<Officer Luda>Heh, if you refuse to move, then die right here.
A

\N<Yuia>The town is in an uproar... What's... this commotion about?
\N<Irime>Yuia-san...!!

\N<Yuia>Irime-san... What happened? What's all this commotion
about...?

\N<Irime>I, I was away from town for a while... and I just got back!
And then... and then!

\N<Irime>Yuia-san... are you listening? Please stay calm and hear me
out?
\N<Yuia>...

\N<Irime>Your wife... Segi... she happened to be at the clinic for a
regular check-up and has been taken hostage by the Luda
gang...
\N<Yuia>Wha...!!??
B
